-- GWT 1.6.0 or later is required.

-- The build requires a GWT_HOME enviornment variable.

-- Eclipse requires a GWT16_HOME classpath variable.


1. Building	
============================================================================
To build a JAR enter:

	ant

Other ANT targets are:

	- build	: for building the JAR and the demo WAR
	- jar	: for building the JAR only (default)
	- war	: for building the WAR only
	- clean
	- javadoc

2. The demo
============================================================================
To run the Showcase demo enter:

	ant hosted

3. Using
============================================================================
To use the library you will need also gwt-dnd.jar, gwtx.jar, 
gwt-beans-binding.jar and gwt-incubator.jar from the lib directory, and 
you have to add:

	<!-- Inherit Mosaic Web Toolkit stuff.                          -->
	<inherits name='org.gwt.mosaic.Mosaic' />

	<!-- Inherit the default GWT Mosaic style sheet. You can change -->
	<!-- the theme of your GWT Mosaic application by uncommenting   -->
	<!-- any one of the following lines.                            -->
	<inherits name='org.gwt.mosaic.theme.standard.Standard' />
	<!-- <inherits name="org.gwt.mosaic.chrome.Chrome"/>            -->
	<!-- <inherits name="org.gwt.mosaic.dark.Dark"/>                -->
	<!-- <inherits name='org.gwt.mosaic.theme.aegean.Aegean' />     -->
 
in your module gwt.xml file.
